This is an extremely beta howto on how to use this profiler.

first, in your ini file add:
;; activate the extension
zend_extension="/path/to/php_pdb.so"
;; set the directory for trace dumps
pdb.dumpdir="/path/to/tracedump/destdir"  

in your php file, add:

apd_set_session_trace(N);

where N is an integer which is formed by masking together:

#define FUNCTION_TRACE 1
#define ARGS_TRACE 2
#define ASSIGNMENT_TRACE 4
#define STATEMENT_TRACE 8
#define MEMORY_TRACE 16
#define TIMING_TRACE 32

I would seriously not recommend using MEMORY_TRACE.  It is very slow and 
does not appear to be accurate (great, huh?)  also ASSIGNMENT_TRACE is
not implemented. So, to turn on all functional traces (TIMING, FUNCTIONS,
and ARGS) use

apd_set_session_trace(35);

run your script.  Output will be written to pdb.dumpdir/apd_dump_<pid>
inside the file is ouput like:

16:37:51(george@wasabi)[~/src/apd]> cat /tmp/apd_dump_31994 


APD - Advanced PHP Debugger Trace File
